capstone.element

Class DynamicObstacle

  • java.lang.Object
    • capstone.element.Element
      • capstone.element.DynamicObstacle
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntelligentObstacle, PatternObstacle, RandomizedObstacle

    public abstract class DynamicObstacle
extends Element
    Abstract class for all dynamic-obstacles, i.e. all obstacles that move. It defines all operations a DynamicObstacle needs on the outside. Minimally, a concrete subclass of this class need only implement the _next method to return the next safe delta according to its dynamic motion.

    • Method Detail

      • Random

        @Deprecated
public static DynamicObstacle Random(Point point,
                                                 Representation representation)
        Deprecated. 
        Factory-method to create a random dynamic-obstacle concrete-object. All dynamic-obstacle types except IntelligentObstacle are deprecated so basically don't use this method.
        Parameters:
        point - The point to construct the dynamic-obstacle at.
        representation - The representation to construct the dynamic-obstacle with.
        Returns:
        An instance of one of the subclasses of DynamicObstacle. Which subclass it is is random.

      • update

        public Point update(Region region,
                    java.util.Set<Point> taken)
        Updates the point in a safe way. Safety here means that any update to the dynamic-obstacle's point will result in the point being: 1. Within the given region. 2. Not on any point included in the given set of taken points. What that update means depends on the concrete class. The dynamic-obstacle could move randomly, according to some pattern etc.
        Parameters:
        region - The region the point of the dynamic-obstacle must be in after updating.
        taken - The set of points the point of the dynamic-obstacle must not be on after updating.
        Returns:
        A valid point fitting both constraints.

      • peekDelta

        public Delta peekDelta(Region region,
                       java.util.Set<Point> taken)
        Returns the next safe Delta, i.e. by what Delta the point of the dynamic-obstacle will move when calling update().
        Parameters:
        region - The region the point of the dynamic-obstacle must be in after the delta would be applied.
        taken - The set of points the point of the dynamic-obstacle must not be on after the delta would be applied.
        Returns:
        A valid delta fitting both constraints.
